race.comment: SCUD (10) began awkwardly then recovered to be beaten under two lengths when resuming over this trip at the Gold Coast last time out. Takes on a better field this time but drops 2.5kgs and strips fitter so she is a serious contender. TARTAGLIA (16) missed the kick and was never a factor at Newcastle most recently. Tackles a deeper field today but escapes the crushing weights he has carried this prep. Wide draw the only concern. CRUEL SUMMER (2) is a chance off a 30-day freshen up with the help of the inside alley. In the money two runs back over 1250m at the Kensington track which is strong form for a race of this standard. SHIHAB (1) is a new arrival in the Glen Milligan stable and returns from a five-month spell. Went well in a recent trial so a bright return looks on the cards. SUMO FISH (15) has won three from four over 1200m at this track. Excellent first-up effort over a shorter trip. Right in the mix.
